Part I - (Prosper Loan Dataset)¶

by (OBI UCHECHI LYDIA)¶

Introduction¶

The dataset is a loan data named Prosper loan. The data contains 113937, and 81 variales. The main purpose is to deduced the variables that might affect the loa status ad also to get ideas aout their relationship using statistics and visualization.

def boxplott(x, y, **kwargs):
    """ Quick hack for creating box plots with seaborn's PairGrid. """
    color = sb.color_palette()[0]
    sb.boxplot(x, y, color=color)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90);

Conclusions¶

The prosper loan project includes 113937 loans wiith 81 variables which are the coulums. The dataset is a big one which at first was diffcult to understand. With visual analyzing, i was able to know the varaibles, to understand the general idea, structure and datatype. Since the data contain some null values, I had to eliminate before exploring, then visualizations.

In bivariate analysis, the relationship among the variables are explored. I observed that monthly loan payment has a strong positive relationshipwith the loan original amount. The loan original amount is positively correlated with monthly income. The borrowerAPR has a strong positive relationship with the Borrow Rate which is a linear trend.

Also, i performed a multivariate analysis to study various relation between status and various variables. From the diagram, i observed that the loan original amount tends to increase for every income range. The borrower rate for defaulter is highfor all employment status.
